commit.message: doc: update ChangeLog for 1.8.0 release
cc: remove parameters from msg_create and capture_launch_thread definition #471

CMake build support revised

- Compiler options '-Wall -pedantic' added
- Definition of _XOPEN_SOURCE_EXTENDED added
- Template configuration header file src/config.h.cmake added
- README updated

See also: https://github.com/irontec/sngrep/pull/462

CMake build adapted to older versions of 'libpcap' which don't provide a pkg-config file

Furthermore CPACK_PACKAGE_NAME and CPACK_PACKAGE_VERSION are set explicitly since this is needed for older CMake versions.

(Tested on Debian Stretch with CMake 3.7.2)
Support for building sngrep using CMake added
main: -F flag should not require extra arguments #461

Redefine usage of POSIX signals.

Use signal SIGUSR1 instead of SIGHUP to detect when to rotate the pcap dump file.
Use signal SIGHUP instead of SIGCONT to detect when the controlling terminal closed.

This signal usage provides that sngrep closes cleanly when its controlling (SSH) terminal closes.
capture: properly check link layer header size before IP reassembly #446
capture: only validate BPF filters against libpcap sources #452
doc: add -r option to man page #451
Fix: typo in comment line

Ensure legacy compatibility with libpcre2 dependency

Co-authored-by: Kaian <Kaian@irontec.com>
[fix] debian pkg dependency to libpcre2-8-0
capture: properly validate WS packet payload size #438
fix remove unused variables and uset getmaxx() or getmaxy() for remaining variables
fix compiler warnings about unused variables
fix typo in message, thanks to lintian
doc: update ChangeLog for 1.7.0 release

Initialize text_outfile to NULL.

'device' and 'outfile' are initialized from 'settings' in the later code,
but 'text_outfile' is not initialized, which may lead to writing to an unknown file.
capture: validate frame has at least IP header before assembly #431
capture: properly validate capture length calculated from IP headers #430
core: stop running when ssh connection has lost #424
hep: disable HEP listen during offline capture mode

Instant convert pcap to txt file (#427)

* add siplify command for saving pcap to txt file

* remove unnecessary printf and commented code

* Refactor siplify into text; minor changes according to pull request review
